## Never Do in API Code

- Never return a full API key after the issuance endpoint
- Never expose internal error details or stack traces in API responses
- Never skip rate limiting on any endpoint
- Never implement quota logic in individual handlers — only in middleware
- Never break the `/api/v1/` contract — add `/api/v2/` for breaking changes
- Never use IP-only rate limiting for API keys — rate limit by key
- Never allow a free-tier key to trigger paid features (PDF, webhooks)
